abstract: Iowa caucusgoers aren’t just asking about the one issue that’s dominating the headlines.
snippet: Iowa caucusgoers aren’t just asking about the one issue that’s dominating the headlines.
lead_paragraph: MARSHALLTOWN, Iowa — With three jurors in the impeachment trial traipsing about Iowa this past weekend, you’d expect someone — anyone! — planning to attend the Iowa caucuses to ask the presidential candidates about impeachment.

abstract: U.S. Republican Senator Mitt Romney said on Monday that it was "increasingly likely" at least four Republican senators would join Democrats in calling for John Bolton, the former White House national security adviser, to testify in the Senate impeachment trial of U.S. President Donald Trump.
snippet: U.S. Republican Senator Mitt Romney said on Monday that it was "increasingly likely" at least four Republican senators would join Democrats in calling for John Bolton, the former White House national security adviser, to testify in the Senate impe...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. Republican Senator Mitt Romney said on Monday that it was "increasingly likely" at least four Republican senators would join Democrats in calling for John Bolton, the former White House national security adviser, to testify in the Senate impeachment trial of U.S. President Donald Trump.
headline_main: 'Increasingly Likely' Republican Senators to Back Call for Bolton to Testify: Romney
headline_print_headline: 'Increasingly Likely' Republican Senators to Back Call for Bolton to Testify: Romney

abstract: Ken Starr — yes, Ken Starr — wonders how America has arrived at the “age of impeachment.”
snippet: Ken Starr — yes, Ken Starr — wonders how America has arrived at the “age of impeachment.”
lead_paragraph: You have to hand it to the legal team defending President Trump in the Senate’s impeachment trial: It sticks to its story, even when confronted by new evidence pretty much demolishing that story.

abstract: Pam Bondi, one of the president’s lawyers, said the defense team would rather have ignored questions about the former vice president and his son.
snippet: Pam Bondi, one of the president’s lawyers, said the defense team would rather have ignored questions about the former vice president and his son.
lead_paragraph: President Trump’s lawyers began their promised assault on former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. and his son, Hunter, on Monday, describing what they said was significant evidence of corruption that made Mr. Trump’s interest in the case proper.
headline_main: Lawyers begin their assault on Joe Biden and his son Hunter.

abstract: A single paper copy in a nondescript envelope arrived at the White House on Dec. 30. Four weeks later, news of John Bolton’s book manuscript about his time as President Donald Trump’s national security adviser has exploded into public view, sending a jolt through the president’s impeachment trial.
snippet: A single paper copy in a nondescript envelope arrived at the White House on Dec. 30. Four weeks later, news of John Bolton’s book manuscript about his time as President Donald Trump’s national security adviser has exploded into public view, sendin...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A single paper copy in a nondescript envelope arrived at the White House on Dec. 30. Four weeks later, news of John Bolton’s book manuscript about his time as President Donald Trump’s national security adviser has exploded into public view, sending a jolt through the president’s impeachment trial.
headline_main: News of Bolton Book Sends Jolt Through Impeachment Trial
headline_print_headline: News of Bolton Book Sends Jolt Through Impeachment Trial

abstract: As the liberal Bernie Sanders tightens his grip in Iowa, more traditional Democrats remain split among his four leading competitors, or are unsure altogether of whom to support.
snippet: As the liberal Bernie Sanders tightens his grip in Iowa, more traditional Democrats remain split among his four leading competitors, or are unsure altogether of whom to support.
lead_paragraph: BETTENDORF, Iowa — As they streamed out of the ballroom following a Scott County fund-raising banquet Saturday night, one after the other Iowa Democrats admitted that they still had not decided whom to support just over a week before the state’s presidential caucuses.
